--- title: "Bringing boring data to life" author: "Uzair Ahmed" date: '2024-05-01' format: revealjs: theme: custom.scss slide-number: true auto-animate: true logo: 'images/logo.jpg' transition: fade incremental: true width: 1600 height: 800 show-slide-number: all footer: '[quarto.org](https://{{< meta prerelease-subdomain >}}quarto.org)' preview-links: auto controls: true code-overflow: wrap chalkboard: true css: custom.css execute: cache: true --- ## ::: {.callout title="Data Cleaning" .fade-in-then-out} **Data cleaning** is a crucial process that involves identifying and correcting errors, inconsistencies, and inaccuracies in datasets. Its importance stems from the significant impact it has on the reliability and effectiveness of data-driven decision-making ::: ![ ](images/data.jpeg){.fragment height="500"} ## {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ::: {.callout-important title="Pros of clean data"} - Improves Accuracy and Reliability of Analysis - Decisions based on clean, high-quality data are more likely to be effective and aligned with business goals - Accurate data allows for a clearer understanding of trends, customer behavior, and market dynamics, enabling organizations to identify opportunities and mitigate risks effectively - Clean data ensures that reports and analyses are trustworthy, leading to greater confidence among stakeholders - Clean data facilitates smoother data integration and processing across different systems and applications - Poor data quality can lead to mistakes like overstocking inventory, misinterpreting customer behavior, and inefficient marketing campaigns, all of which can result in significant financial losses ::: ## {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ::: {.callout-warning title="What to watch out for"} - Garbage in, garbage out - Avoids costly errors - Storage costs - Regulatory requirements - Security risks ::: ![ ](images/messy.jpeg){fig-align="center" width="75%"} # Data Process {transition="zoom" transition-speed="slow"} ## Data Process {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ![ ](images/process.png){fig-align="center" width="100%"} ## Data Investigation {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} :::: {.columns} ::: {.column width="100%"} ::: {#90e62f12 .cell output-location='column' execution_count=3} ``` {.python .cell-code code-line-numbers="1|2"} print(f"Rows: {df.shape[0]}") print(f"Columns: {df.shape[1]}") ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` Rows: 1460 Columns: 81 ``` ::: ::: ::: :::: ## Data Investigation {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ::: {#0122cae6 .cell execution_count=4} ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=3} ```{=html}

``` ::: ::: ## Missing Values..... {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ::: {#8be4d031 .cell output-location='column-fragment' execution_count=5} ``` {.python .cell-code .code-overflow-wrap} missing=(df.isnull().sum() / len(df)) * 100 ## Missing percentage > 0 missing=missing[missing > 0] ## Convert to dataframe and sort values missing_df=pd.DataFrame({'Missing Values' : missing}) missing_df=missing_df['Missing Values'].sort_values(ascending = False) f, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6,6)) sns.barplot(x=missing_df.index, y=missing_df.values, ax=ax) plt.title('Columns with missing Values', fontsize = 14) plt.xlabel('', fontsize = 10) plt.ylabel('%', fontsize = 10) plt.xticks(rotation = 'vertical') plt.show() ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![](slideshow_files/figure-revealjs/cell-5-output-1.png){width=519 height=590} ::: ::: ## Remove Columns {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ::: {#4c06efec .cell output-location='column' execution_count=6} ``` {.python .cell-code} cols_to_drop = missing[missing > 60].index df_cleaned = df.drop(columns=cols_to_drop) # Compare the number of columns compare_data={ 'Data': ['Raw', 'Cleaned Data'], 'Columns': [df.shape[1], df_cleaned.shape[1]] } print(pd.DataFrame(compare_data)) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` Data Columns 0 Raw 81 1 Cleaned Data 77 ``` ::: ::: ## Missing value imputation {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ### Filling with None ::: {#a6389fec .cell output-location='column-fragment' execution_count=7} ``` {.python .cell-code .code-overflow-wrap} cols=['FireplaceQu', 'GarageType', 'GarageFinish', 'GarageQual', 'GarageCond', 'BsmtQual', 'BsmtCond', 'BsmtExposure', 'BsmtFinType1', 'BsmtFinType2', 'MasVnrType', 'MSSubClass'] for col in cols: df_cleaned[col] = df_cleaned[col].fillna('None') df_cleaned['FireplaceQu'].value_counts() ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=6} ``` FireplaceQu None 690 Gd 380 TA 313 Fa 33 Ex 24 Po 20 Name: count, dtype: int64 ``` ::: ::: ## Missing value imputation {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ### Filling with 0 ::: {#66f50afc .cell output-location='column-fragment' execution_count=8} ``` {.python .cell-code .code-overflow-wrap} columns = ['BsmtFinSF1', 'BsmtFinSF2', 'BsmtUnfSF', 'TotalBsmtSF', 'BsmtFullBath', 'BsmtHalfBath', 'MasVnrArea', 'GarageYrBlt', 'GarageArea', 'GarageCars'] for col in columns: df_cleaned[col] = df_cleaned[col].fillna(0) print(df_cleaned[cols].isnull().sum()) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` FireplaceQu 0 GarageType 0 GarageFinish 0 GarageQual 0 GarageCond 0 BsmtQual 0 BsmtCond 0 BsmtExposure 0 BsmtFinType1 0 BsmtFinType2 0 MasVnrType 0 MSSubClass 0 dtype: int64 ``` ::: ::: ## Missing value imputation {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ### Filling with Median ::: {#cd35d68c .cell output-location='fragment' execution_count=9} ``` {.python .cell-code} df_cleaned["LotFrontage"] = df_cleaned.groupby("Neighborhood")["LotFrontage"].transform( lambda x: x.fillna(x.median())) lot_front = df_cleaned["LotFrontage"].isnull().sum() print(f"Neighborhoods with remaining missing LotFrontage: {lot_front}") ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` Neighborhoods with remaining missing LotFrontage: 0 ``` ::: ::: ## Remove columns with near zero variance {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ### Identify Near Zero variance ::: {#80aeb9ba .cell output-location='fragment' execution_count=10} ``` {.python .cell-code} near_zero_variance_cols = [] for col in df_cleaned.select_dtypes(include='object').columns: value_counts = df[col].value_counts(normalize=True) if len(value_counts) > 0 and value_counts.iloc[0] >= 0.8: near_zero_variance_cols.append(col) print(near_zero_variance_cols) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` ['Street', 'LandContour', 'Utilities', 'LandSlope', 'Condition1', 'Condition2', 'BldgType', 'RoofMatl', 'ExterCond', 'BsmtCond', 'BsmtFinType2', 'Heating', 'CentralAir', 'Electrical', 'Functional', 'GarageQual', 'GarageCond', 'PavedDrive', 'SaleType', 'SaleCondition'] ``` ::: ::: ## Remove columns with near zero variance {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ### Drop the near zero variance ::: {#73fa6921 .cell output-location='fragment' execution_count=11} ``` {.python .cell-code} df_cleaned = df_cleaned.drop(columns=near_zero_variance_cols) compare_data = { 'Dataset': ['Raw Data', 'Cleaned Data'], 'Number of Columns': [df.shape[1], df_cleaned.shape[1]] } print(pd.DataFrame(compare_data).to_string(index=False)) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` Dataset Number of Columns Raw Data 81 Cleaned Data 57 ``` ::: ::: ## So, How does the cleaned data look like? {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ### Take a Peak ::: {#4dacc148 .cell output-location='fragment' execution_count=12} ``` {.python .cell-code} print(df_cleaned.isnull().sum()) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` Id 0 MSSubClass 0 MSZoning 0 LotFrontage 0 LotArea 0 LotShape 0 LotConfig 0 Neighborhood 0 HouseStyle 0 OverallQual 0 OverallCond 0 YearBuilt 0 YearRemodAdd 0 RoofStyle 0 Exterior1st 0 Exterior2nd 0 MasVnrType 0 MasVnrArea 0 ExterQual 0 Foundation 0 BsmtQual 0 BsmtExposure 0 BsmtFinType1 0 BsmtFinSF1 0 BsmtFinSF2 0 BsmtUnfSF 0 TotalBsmtSF 0 HeatingQC 0 1stFlrSF 0 2ndFlrSF 0 LowQualFinSF 0 GrLivArea 0 BsmtFullBath 0 BsmtHalfBath 0 FullBath 0 HalfBath 0 BedroomAbvGr 0 KitchenAbvGr 0 KitchenQual 0 TotRmsAbvGrd 0 Fireplaces 0 FireplaceQu 0 GarageType 0 GarageYrBlt 0 GarageFinish 0 GarageCars 0 GarageArea 0 WoodDeckSF 0 OpenPorchSF 0 EnclosedPorch 0 3SsnPorch 0 ScreenPorch 0 PoolArea 0 MiscVal 0 MoSold 0 YrSold 0 SalePrice 0 dtype: int64 ``` ::: ::: ## And what about the column types? {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ::: {#b80dcde8 .cell output-location='fragment' execution_count=13} ``` {.python .cell-code} print(df_cleaned.dtypes) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` Id int64 MSSubClass int64 MSZoning object LotFrontage float64 LotArea int64 LotShape object LotConfig object Neighborhood object HouseStyle object OverallQual int64 OverallCond int64 YearBuilt int64 YearRemodAdd int64 RoofStyle object Exterior1st object Exterior2nd object MasVnrType object MasVnrArea float64 ExterQual object Foundation object BsmtQual object BsmtExposure object BsmtFinType1 object BsmtFinSF1 int64 BsmtFinSF2 int64 BsmtUnfSF int64 TotalBsmtSF int64 HeatingQC object 1stFlrSF int64 2ndFlrSF int64 LowQualFinSF int64 GrLivArea int64 BsmtFullBath int64 BsmtHalfBath int64 FullBath int64 HalfBath int64 BedroomAbvGr int64 KitchenAbvGr int64 KitchenQual object TotRmsAbvGrd int64 Fireplaces int64 FireplaceQu object GarageType object GarageYrBlt float64 GarageFinish object GarageCars int64 GarageArea int64 WoodDeckSF int64 OpenPorchSF int64 EnclosedPorch int64 3SsnPorch int64 ScreenPorch int64 PoolArea int64 MiscVal int64 MoSold int64 YrSold int64 SalePrice int64 dtype: object ``` ::: ::: ## {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ### Numeric to Categorical ::: {#8fe8ab32 .cell output-location='column-fragment' execution_count=14} ``` {.python .cell-code} cols = ["MSSubClass", "OverallCond", "YrSold", "MoSold"] for col in cols: df_cleaned[col]=df_cleaned[col].astype(str) print(df_cleaned[cols].dtypes) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` MSSubClass object OverallCond object YrSold object MoSold object dtype: object ``` ::: ::: # Feature Engineering {transition="zoom" transition-speed="slow"} ## Total Area {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ::: {#13317ab8 .cell output-location='fragment' execution_count=15} ``` {.python .cell-code} df_cleaned['TotalArea'] = df_cleaned['TotalBsmtSF'] + df_cleaned['1stFlrSF'] + df_cleaned['2ndFlrSF'] df_cleaned[['TotalBsmtSF', '1stFlrSF', '2ndFlrSF', 'TotalArea']].head() ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display execution_count=14} ```{=html}

Price vs Living Area {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ### With Outlier ::: {#41c9acb7 .cell output-location='fragment' execution_count=17} ``` {.python .cell-code} plt.scatter(df_cleaned['GrLivArea'], df_cleaned['SalePrice']) plt.xlabel('Living Area') plt.ylabel('Sale Price') plt.show() ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![](slideshow_files/figure-revealjs/cell-17-output-1.png){width=842 height=429} ::: ::: ## Price vs Total Area {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ### Without Outlier ::: {#2c42732e .cell output-location='fragment' execution_count=18} ``` {.python .cell-code} df_cleaned = df_cleaned.drop(df_cleaned[(df_cleaned['GrLivArea'] > 4000) & (df_cleaned['SalePrice'] < 300000)].index) plt.scatter(df_cleaned['TotalArea'], df_cleaned['SalePrice']) plt.title('') plt.xlabel('Total Area') plt.ylabel('Sale Price') plt.show() ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![](slideshow_files/figure-revealjs/cell-18-output-1.png){width=842 height=429} ::: ::: ## Price vs Overall Quality {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ::: {#5575d8eb .cell output-location='fragment' execution_count=20} ``` {.python .cell-code} plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5)) sns.boxplot(x = df_cleaned['Neighborhood'], y = df_cleaned['SalePrice']) plt.title('Sales Price And Neighbourhood') plt.xticks(rotation = 90) plt.show() ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![](slideshow_files/figure-revealjs/cell-20-output-1.png){width=990 height=501} ::: ::: ## Price vs House Style {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ::: {#675c967b .cell output-location='fragment' execution_count=21} ``` {.python .cell-code} plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5)) sns.boxplot(x = df_cleaned['HouseStyle'], y = df_cleaned['SalePrice']) plt.xticks(rotation = 90) plt.show() ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ![](slideshow_files/figure-revealjs/cell-21-output-1.png){width=990 height=462} ::: ::: ## Statistics {transition="concave" transition-speed="slow"} ::: {#b8ef6383 .cell output-location='slide' execution_count=22} ``` {.python .cell-code} houses_sold_per_neighborhood = df_cleaned.groupby('Neighborhood').size().reset_index(name='Number of Houses Sold') average_price_per_neighborhood = df_cleaned.groupby('Neighborhood')['SalePrice'].mean().reset_index(name='Average Sale Price') neighborhood_sales_summary = pd.merge(houses_sold_per_neighborhood, average_price_per_neighborhood, on='Neighborhood') show(neighborhood_sales_summary, scrollY="300px", scrollCollapse=True, paging=False, buttons=["copyHtml5", "csvHtml5", "excelHtml5"], classes="display nowrap table_with_monospace_font", searching=False) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display} ```{=html}
